{"id":"7185","name":"Get Screen Density [JS1]","tagline":"A JavaScript one-liner to find out the pixel density of the screen","icon":"ios12 c255 g59781","latest":"22249","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>A single line of JavaScript to find out pixel density of the screen. LED screens usually result in a 2 and OLED ones in a 3. This can be used to determine the real resolution of the screen, or to decide the quality of the assets to download.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>No error checking</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://editor.scpl.dev/?scpl=%40Icon%20microscope%0A%40Color%20darkgray%0AComment%20%22A%20JavaScript%20one-liner%20to%20find%20out%20the%20pixel%20density%20of%20the%20screen%20%E2%80%94%20%40atnbueno%20%282020-10-25%29%5Cn%5Cn-%20LED%20screens%20usually%20result%20in%20a%202%20and%20OLED%20ones%20in%20a%203%5Cn-%20No%20error%20checking%22%0AURL%20%22data%3Atext%2Fhtml%2C%3Cscript%3Edocument.write%28window.devicePixelRatio%29%3C%2Fscript%3E%22%20-%3E%20mv%3AURL%0AGetFileofType%20%22com.apple.webarchive%22%20-%3E%20mv%3A%22Get%20File%20of%20Type%22%0AShowResult%20mv%3A%22Get%20File%20of%20Type%22%7Bas%3A%20text%7D\">ScPL source</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/API/Window/devicePixelRatio\"><code>Window.devicePixelRatio</code> documentation at MDN</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Don't download the shortcut</h4>\n<p>If you just want the code, there's no need to download the shortcut. Copy this and paste it in a \"URL\" action:</p>\n<pre><code>data:text/html,&lt;script&gt;document.write(window.devicePixelRatio)&lt;/script&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Add a \"Get File of Type\" with type <code>com.apple.webarchive</code> below, and its output will be the pixel density of the screen. That's all.</p>\n<p>I use \"Get File of Type\" instead of \"Get Contents of Webpage\" to avoid that the user is misleading told that the shortcut uses Safari.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0.0 - Oct. 25, 2020, 10:46 a.m.</strong></p>"}